A GYRO (or more properly "gyros") is a sandwich (or, if you like a not-a-sandwich) consisting of pita bread surrounding hot sliced meat that has been cooked on a vertical spit, with tomatoes, onions and tzatziki (a cucumber-based cream sauce).  Lettuce and fries (chips) are sometimes also added.

You might know it as a döner kebab, which is the Turkish name.  Both names mean "turning" in their original languages.  In other countries, this dish or something very similar is called schawarma or al pastor.

